ESPeccy - Sinclair ZX Spectrum emulator for the Espressif ESP32 SoC

Copyright (c) 2024 Juan José Ponteprino [SplinterGU]
https://github.com/SplinterGU/ESPeccy

This project is based on previous work from the following contributors:

1. **ESPectrum** - Original project for the ESP32
   - Authors: Víctor Iborra [Eremus] and David Crespo [dcrespo3d]
   - Repository: https://github.com/EremusOne/ZX-ESPectrum-IDF
   - Description: ESPectrum is an emulator of the Sinclair ZX Spectrum, ported to the Espressif ESP32 platform.

2. **ZX-ESPectrum-Wiimote** - Support for Wiimote input
   - Author: David Crespo [dcrespo3d]
   - Repository: https://github.com/dcrespo3d/ZX-ESPectrum-Wiimote
   - Description: A project that enabled interaction with the ZX Spectrum emulator through Wiimote controllers.

3. **ZX-ESPectrum** - Original ZX Spectrum emulator for ESP32
   - Authors: Ramón Martinez and Jorge Fuertes
   - Repository: https://github.com/rampa069/ZX-ESPectrum
   - Description: Another iteration of a ZX Spectrum emulator, contributing to the ESP32 ecosystem.

4. **paseVGA** - VGA output for ZX Spectrum emulation
   - Author: Pete Todd
   - Repository: https://github.com/retrogubbins/paseVGA
   - Description: This project contributed to the VGA output functionality for ZX Spectrum emulators.

---

### Contributions:

ESPeccy is a project that extends and builds upon the work of the above-mentioned projects, adding numerous new features and improvements.

